        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 3 at 3:13PM EDT by NWS Burlington VT</headline>
        <description>At 312 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Wells, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chester, Woodstock, Cavendish, Ludlow Village, Middletown Springs,
Perkinsville Village, Wallingford, Mt. Holly, Mt. Tabor, Rutland -
Southern Vermont Airport, Plymouth, Wells, Pawlet, Mount Holly,
Ludlow, Mount Tabor, Weston, Tinmouth, Shrewsbury, and Danby.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
